pageContext.claim: “In Detroit, turnout was 139% of registered voters. Think of that. So you had 139% of the people in Detroit voting.”
pageContext.analysis: "Trump's claim is false," <a target="_blank" href="https://www.freep.com/story/news/local/michigan/detroit/2021/01/06/fact-check-congressional-certification-electoral-college-votes/4143866001/">said the Detroit Free Press". "The city's official results show a turnout rate of 50.88% in the Nov. 3 election. Trump's incorrect turnout rate for Detroit comes from an affidavit filed in support of a lawsuit rejected in court that made wildly inaccurate allegations about turnout rates in Michigan townships and cities."
